document_data.History:
In the {{YearlinkName|1479}}, Fetterfist's gang attacked a caravan near Ravens Bluff and delivered their captives to the drow beneath the city.  A young noblewoman named [[Seila Norwood]] was among the slaves.

Later, Balathorp was hired by the drow to return [[Jack Ravenwild]] to imprisonment in their underground realm. Jack tricked Balathorp into an ambush at a warehouse and captured him with the help of the [[Blue Wyverns]]. Thinking the city watch would imprison Balathorp, Jack tied him up in the warehouse and left a note describing Balathorp's crimes. Unfortunately, the city magistrates didn't believe a noble of Balathorp's stature could be a slaver so they set him free.{{Cite digital book/Prince of Ravens/Kindle|4986|11}}

Shortly thereafter, Balathorp's gang, along with drow warriors, attacked a noble revel with the intent of killing most of the nobles present and enslaving the remainder.{{Cite digital book/Prince of Ravens/Kindle|4263|12}} [[Marden Norwood|Lord Norwood]] and [[Myrkyssa Jelan]] led an armed force into the Underdark to rescue the captives. Balathorp attempted to escape to the surface with his prisoners but he was run through by Jack Ravenwild's blade.{{Cite digital book/Prince of Ravens/Kindle|4720|13}}
